# Database Structure (Assuming a Relational Database):

1. User Table:
UserID (Primary Key)
Username
Password (Hashed and Salted)

2. Event Table:
EventID (Primary Key)
Title
Date
Venue

3. Ticket Table:
TicketID (Primary Key)
EventID (Foreign Key referencing Event Table)
Price
AvailableQuantity
TotalQuantity

4. Order Table:
OrderID (Primary Key)
UserID (Foreign Key referencing User Table)
EventID (Foreign Key referencing Event Table)
Quantity
TotalPrice
OrderDate


# RESTful Endpoints:

1. User Authentication:
POST /auth/login - User login.
POST /auth/register - User registration.

2. Event Operations:
GET /events - Retrieve a list of events.
GET /events/{eventID} - Retrieve details of a specific event.
POST /events - Create a new event (requires authentication).
PUT /events/{eventID} - Update details of a specific event (requires authentication).
DELETE /events/{eventID} - Delete a specific event (requires authentication).

3. Ticket Operations:
GET /events/{eventID}/tickets - Retrieve available tickets for a specific event.
GET /tickets/{ticketID} - Retrieve details of a specific ticket.
POST /events/{eventID}/tickets/order - Order tickets for a specific event (requires authentication).
PUT /tickets/{ticketID} - Update details of a specific ticket (requires authentication).
DELETE /tickets/{ticketID} - Delete a specific ticket (requires authentication).

4. Order Operations:
GET /orders - Retrieve a list of user orders (requires authentication).
GET /orders/{orderID} - Retrieve details of a specific order (requires authentication).
DELETE /orders/{orderID} - Cancel a specific order (requires authentication).